cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CC

This paper discusses a middleware environment for managing single-instance multi-tenant cloud applications, which involves coordination between services and variations in functional and performance requirements for different tenants. This topic is relevant to several computer science sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). However, given the focus on managing and coordinating services in a cloud environment, Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) is the most likely sub-category. Software Engineering (cs.SE) is also likely given the emphasis on middleware and managing software applications. Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) is relevant due to the multi-tenant aspect of the cloud application, while Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) are less likely but still possible due to the focus on managing and coordinating services in a complex environment.
